tags: And good god I miss my Doctor
summary: If you didn’t know I have been binge-watching Doctor Who again to catch up And I’m inching ever-closer to the end of Ten’s run...
body:
If you didn’t know

I have been binge-watching Doctor Who again to catch up

And I’m inching ever-closer to the end of Ten’s run

And my heart has been slowly breaking for two or three days

I love it and I hate it all at once

And somehow it hurts more than the first time

And somehow I keep craving more

And all the while I keep plotting to write a fic where things happen a little differently, where Rose doesn’t leave, where Donna doesn’t forget, where plot points are shifted and little things change…where things are different, and things are better, and where Ten doesn’t regenerate alone because god above that broke my heart to watch

And three days

And for three days my heart has been aching and my mind reeling and every episode is reliving amazing memories and experiencing the wonder again

I had forgotten just how much I love and adore this show

summary: Re: Director's cut: 1) Keys to the Kingdom: the last sentence (and the whole story): how is Carolina connected to Freya? 2) ☆ :)
question: Re: Director's cut: 1) Keys to the Kingdom: the last sentence (and the whole story): how is Carolina connected to Freya? 2) ☆ :)
answer:
You caught that, ha!

Freya’s a clever woman, so she knows that Aiden is down, but he won’t - can’t - stay down. Carolina is … a fail safe. What Freya doesn’t know is that Carolina might not be as dedicated as she thinks to Freya’s plan for her.

Keys to the Kingdom
